Description: Thirty-six fragments of a papyrus with a Byzantine Greek protocol text written on one side, along the fibres.
Curator's comments: On the byzantine Greek protocol: Delattre, A. La reutilisation des protocoles aux epoques byzantines et arabe, J. Frosen et al. (eds) Proceedings of the 24th International Congress of Papyrology, Helsinki, 1-7 August, 2004, 2007, pp. 215-220; Diethart, J., Feissel, D., & Gascou, J. (1994). Les prôtokolla des papyrus byzantins du Ve au VIIe siècle. Tyche, 9, 9–40. The five-sixe line long protocols were used in the 6th-7th centuries.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380793) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380793)
